I’ve been reading/learning a lot. 😅
📚🎓 Almost done. #ASU #Graduate Actually, never done.

Just leveled up in the game of life – new career mode unlocked. Some of you may or may not know, but for the last three years I’ve been working hard on a brand new professional path. 
As an ADHD student, immigrant, athlete and musician, life has shown me all the riches it has to offer and in 2020 I was offered a full ride scholarship from Uber to attend Arizona State University. 
Three years later, December 11th of 2023, I am graduating from ASU’s Fulton Teachers College with a Bachelor of Arts in Education degree with a Spanish Language and Culture minor. Summa Cum Laude. 📚 
Special thanks to my future wife @miss_felty and to our families for the help and support!
Watch ceremony virtually at http://ustream.tv/asutv 
#asugrad #asuonline #teacher #professor @asuonline
